  "Low-level clouds (0-2 km)": "",
  "Mid-level clouds (2-6 km)": "",
  "The prefix 'alto-' in cloud classification indicates mid-level clouds found at altitudes between approximately 2 and 6 kilometers, such as altostratus (layered) and altocumulus (puffy) clouds.": "",
