  "A rain shadow effect creating localized freezing": "",
  "Temperatures that are too warm for ice to form": "",
  "Very weak updrafts that cannot support ice particles": "",
  "Large hailstones require very strong updrafts (often exceeding 160 km/h for golf-ball-sized hail) to keep the growing ice particles suspended in the cloud long enough to accumulate multiple layers of ice through repeated trips above the freezing level.": "",
